						<summary>

						<p>Boulder in a field survey No. 1409 on the way to Sangamēśvaram.</p>						

						<p>IṞEGEYA MAHARĀJU.</p>						

						<p>976 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated Śaka 898, Kārtika, śu. 11 <hi rend="italic">(ēkādasi)</hi> Friday corresponding to October 6, 976 A.D. The cyclic year was Dhātri.</p>						

						<p>It registers the tax free gift measuring 50 <hi rend="italic">maṛuturu</hi> of land situated to the north of Magamūru in Animela and 7 <hi rend="italic">puṭṭis</hi> of paddy <hi rend="italic">(vaḍlu)</hi> at Poḍatiti to Suriyakramadhāḷu <hi rend="italic">(krama-pāṭhi ?)</hi> as <hi rend="italic">ēkōdhishṭa bhukta dakshiṇa</hi> by Iṟegeya mahārāju, for the merit of his father <hi rend="italic">(tama-Ayya)</hi> Be[jayi]ta mahārāju.</p>						

						</summary>
